00:51:25,207 --> 00:51:27,459
Hey, Crystal.

830
00:51:27,543 --> 00:51:29,544
Miss Donnelly said to give you these.

831
00:51:29,628 --> 00:51:31,337
OK. I'll be right down.

832
00:51:33,758 --> 00:51:35,175
What?

833
00:51:36,427 --> 00:51:38,261
And for either of my opponents to suggest

834
00:51:38,345 --> 00:51:42,932
that downtown development comes
at the expense of our city's neighborhoods,

835
00:51:43,017 --> 00:51:47,061
well, that's just unfair and divisive.

836
00:51:47,146 --> 00:51:50,190
For them to suggest
that my administration

837
00:51:50,274 --> 00:51:53,276
has not been responsive, well...

838
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:55,779
Economic development
cannot be a Band-Aid.

839
00:51:55,863 --> 00:51:59,491
It is a long-term process
that requires commitment

840
00:51:59,575 --> 00:52:02,452
to retraining our workforce
and, as I said before,

841
00:52:02,536 --> 00:52:05,413
this can only be successful
in a city where people feel safe.

842
00:52:05,498 --> 00:52:09,125
So before we can begin to think
about luring new industries to Baltimore,

843
00:52:09,210 --> 00:52:11,628
we need to think about
how we can make these neighborhoods

844
00:52:11,712 --> 00:52:13,963
and this city safe once again.

845
00:52:14,048 --> 00:52:18,384
Mr. Carcetti may think
it's in his interests to exploit people's fears.

846
00:52:18,469 --> 00:52:21,888
He's been doing it throughout this campaign.

847
00:52:21,972 --> 00:52:25,141
I'm offended by it, personally. But the fact is,

848
00:52:25,226 --> 00:52:28,728
that violent crime is down city-wide,

849
00:52:28,813 --> 00:52:32,690
and our police department
is working hard to keep it that way,

850
00:52:32,775 --> 00:52:35,735
and will continue to do so
under my administration.

851
00:52:35,820 --> 00:52:38,780
Councilman Carcetti,
you have two minutes to respond.

852
00:52:39,156 --> 00:52:42,784
Does anyone in this room really believe
that crime is down in Baltimore?

853
00:52:42,868 --> 00:52:44,160
You calling me a liar, Tommy?

854
00:52:44,245 --> 00:52:46,454
Gentleman, please. No personal interactions.

855
00:52:46,539 --> 00:52:49,332
- Councilman Carcetti.
- Can the mayor honestly tell

856
00:52:49,416 --> 00:52:51,835
the people of Rosemont,
of Belair Edison,

857
00:52:51,919 --> 00:52:56,089
of Highlandtown or Cherry Hill
there's less drug-dealing, less violence?

858
00:52:56,340 --> 00:52:58,550
Any statistics coming
from the police department

859
00:52:58,634 --> 00:53:02,178
cannot be trusted, because under this mayor,
the police are more concerned

860
00:53:02,263 --> 00:53:05,431
with protecting Clarence Royce politically
than fighting crime.

861
00:53:05,766 --> 00:53:08,434
There's no leadership
and morale has never been lower.

862
00:53:08,519 --> 00:53:09,727
I'll change that.

863
00:53:09,812 --> 00:53:12,105
It's business as usual down at City Hall

864
00:53:12,189 --> 00:53:14,607
and as a result, our response to crime

865
00:53:14,692 --> 00:53:17,151
has been characterized time and time again

866
00:53:17,236 --> 00:53:19,612
by wanton indifference.

867
00:53:19,697 --> 00:53:21,072
..32 yards!

868
00:53:21,156 --> 00:53:24,450
What do I mean by business as usual?

869
00:53:24,535 --> 00:53:26,703
What do I mean by wanton indifference?

870
00:53:26,787 --> 00:53:31,124
Well, last night
in West Baltimore, on Lanvale Street,

871
00:53:31,208 --> 00:53:33,751
another citizen was shot and killed.

872
00:53:33,836 --> 00:53:37,547
This victim was a key witness
in a drug case that had yet to come to court.

873
00:53:37,631 --> 00:53:40,717
Courageously, this man had agreed to testify

874
00:53:40,801 --> 00:53:42,510
in two weeks' time in that case.

875
00:53:42,595 --> 00:53:46,764
The police should have been protecting him.
They were not, and he was murdered.

876
00:53:47,725 --> 00:53:49,517
- Oh, shit.
- Why? Because this mayor...

877
00:53:49,602 --> 00:53:53,521
- You're prime-time, Eddie.
- ..would not spend the money to protect him.

878
00:53:53,606 --> 00:53:55,440
Now I have no doubt
that in a moment or two

879
00:53:55,524 --> 00:53:58,443
Clarence Royce will accuse me
of exploiting this man's death

880
00:53:58,527 --> 00:54:03,197
for my own political purpose,
but the truth is, a year ago

881
00:54:03,282 --> 00:54:06,326
I wrote the mayor a letter.
I have copies for anyone who wants one.

882
00:54:06,410 --> 00:54:10,413
I begged him to spend the money
and make witness protection a priority.

883
00:54:10,497 --> 00:54:11,581
He ignored me.

884
00:54:12,041 --> 00:54:15,418
I even teamed up with our legislative leaders,
Delegate Watkins and others,

885
00:54:15,502 --> 00:54:18,588
to get matching funds
for witness protection approved in Annapolis.

886
00:54:18,672 --> 00:54:20,798
And incredibly those matching funds

887
00:54:20,883 --> 00:54:22,717
were never claimed by this administration.

888
00:54:22,801 --> 00:54:25,094
Now to mention this now may be exploitive,

889
00:54:25,179 --> 00:54:27,555
I don't know, I only know it's true,

890
00:54:27,640 --> 00:54:30,558
and on such truths I ask the voters of our city

891
00:54:30,643 --> 00:54:32,977
to consider a change.

892
00:54:36,941 --> 00:54:41,277
Folks, please, hold your applause
until after the round of questions is over.

893
00:54:41,362 --> 00:54:42,487
Mayor Royce?

894
00:54:42,613 --> 00:54:44,989
No more surprises, huh?

895
00:54:45,950 --> 00:54:49,577
I am unaware of the specifics
of the incident

896
00:54:49,662 --> 00:54:51,663
to which Councilman Carcetti is referring,

897
00:54:52,498 --> 00:54:55,249
so I can't answer that directly,

898
00:54:55,334 --> 00:55:01,172
however, I can say
that this city places the highest priority

899
00:55:01,256 --> 00:55:04,258
on protecting those citizens
who come forward to testify,

900
00:55:04,343 --> 00:55:07,178
and we will continue to do so.

901
00:55:07,262 --> 00:55:11,182
Mr. Carcetti states that he wrote a letter

902
00:55:11,266 --> 00:55:14,268
expressing his concerns,
and I'm sure that he did.

903
00:55:14,353 --> 00:55:17,063
I mean, it's easy enough to write letters

904
00:55:17,147 --> 00:55:19,732
when all you have to do is write letters.

905
00:55:20,109 --> 00:55:23,111
But when you are required

906
00:55:23,195 --> 00:55:25,738
to run a city

907
00:55:25,823 --> 00:55:28,574
on limited resources,

908
00:55:28,659 --> 00:55:30,910
and balance priorities,

909
00:55:30,995 --> 00:55:33,830
well, then...well, then you understand

910
00:55:33,914 --> 00:55:38,084
